message.content:
cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with monocular object localization and shape estimation using semantic cues from vehicles in the scene. 
2. cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as the paper discusses the task of accurate localization of other traffic participants in autonomous driving systems. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possible category as the proposed approach uses a local bundle-adjustment like procedure that simultaneously estimates the pose and shape of the vehicles. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with developing an intelligent system for object localization and shape estimation on non-planar surfaces. 
5. cs.GR (Graphics) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with approximating road surfaces by local planar patches and estimating the orientation of the local ground plane on which the vehicle stands.
